Class JoinOperator<K,V1,V2,VR>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.heron.api.bolt.BaseWindowedBolt

        • org.apache.heron.streamlet.impl.operators.JoinOperator<K,V1,V2,VR>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, IWindowedBolt, IComponent, IStreamletOperator<V1,VR>, IStreamletWindowOperator<V1,VR>

    public class JoinOperator<K,V1,V2,VR>
extends StreamletWindowOperator<V1,VR>
    JoinOperator is the bolt that implements the join/leftJoin/innerJoin functionality. It embeds the logic of the type of join(outer, left, inner) which it takes in as a config parameter. Also taken as parameters are which source is left and right. This is needed for the semantics of outer/left/inner joins.
